{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17633177","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17633177"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T17:51:41+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T17:51:41+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17469"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17469","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17469"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.86,0.05,0.1,0,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10159"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70808"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10159","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10159"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17469"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56274"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"5326"},{"type":"tags","id":"5522"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"23759"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23806"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70808","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/70808"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 19-year-old woman presents to the Emergency Department with vaginal bleeding and abdominal pain. She appears withdrawn and anxious. An older man who claims to be her uncle insists on remaining present during the consultation and answers most questions directed to the patient. The woman has no identification documents and is unable to provide a residential address.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the concerning social circumstance that should be considered?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["The exploitation of people through force, fraud, or coercion","Intimate partner violence in a consensual relationship","Cultural practices requiring male family member presence","Language barrier requiring family translation","Developmental delay requiring caregiver support"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThe exploitation of people through force, fraud, or coercion\u003C/strong\u003E (human trafficking) should be considered given multiple concerning indicators: lack of identification, restricted communication, controlling companion, and signs of possible abuse.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIntimate partner violence in a consensual relationship\u003C/strong\u003E: while this can present similarly, the combination of indicators including lack of documentation and unclear living situation suggests trafficking.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECultural practices requiring male family member presence\u003C/strong\u003E: while some cultures have such practices, the concerning elements extend beyond just male accompaniment.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELanguage barrier requiring family translation\u003C/strong\u003E: this scenario does not indicate any language difficulties, and professional interpreters should be used when needed.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDevelopmental delay requiring caregiver support\u003C/strong\u003E: no evidence suggests cognitive impairment; the controlling behaviour appears coercive rather than supportive.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHealthcare providers should be alert to trafficking indicators including restricted communication, lack of identification, signs of abuse, controlling companions, and inability to provide basic personal information. When trafficking is suspected, providers should follow institutional protocols and involve appropriate authorities.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Human trafficking involves the exploitation of people through force, fraud, or coercion for purposes including forced labour and sexual exploitation.","Healthcare workers may encounter trafficking victims seeking medical care and should know common indicators.","Common indicators of trafficking include restricted communication, lack of identification, signs of abuse, and controlling companions."],"references":["Combs MA, Arnold T. Human Trafficking: Empowering Healthcare Providers and Community Partners as Advocates for Victims. J Holist Nurs. 2022;40(3):295-301. doi:10.1177/08980101211045554"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56274"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17469"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56274","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/56274"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-16T14:11:49+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-16T14:12:49+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10159"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70808"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"rela